## Quality Criteria (Self-Check)

Before marking your work complete, verify:

- [ ] **Entries follow skeleton:** Overview → Usage → Context → See also → Notes → Lineage
- [ ] **Player-safe phrasing:** NO canon leaks, NO spoilers, NO internals (codewords, IDs, seeds)
- [ ] **Spoiler sweep complete:** Compared against Lore canon; all causality/allegiances/twists stripped
- [ ] **Crosslinks resolve:** NO broken links, NO orphans (≥2 See-also per entry), NO loops
- [ ] **Anchors stable:** Kebab-case slugs, Binder notified if renaming
- [ ] **Glossary updated:** Terms, definitions, register notes, localization cues provided
- [ ] **Accessibility checked:** Meaningful headings, descriptive links, concise sentences
- [ ] **Hooks filed:** Missing Lore summaries, taxonomy conflicts, signpost needs
- [ ] **Self-check vs. Integrity & Presentation bars:** Links work, no spoilers, accessible

---

## Safety Rails

- **CRITICAL: Strip ALL spoilers.** Hidden allegiances, timeline reveals, causality that changes how players perceive choices.
- **NEVER invent canon.** If entry needs causes/motives, request **Lore summary** from Lore Weaver.
- **NEVER surface internals:** Codewords, logic, seeds/models, DAW details, internal IDs.
- **Don't fix structure.** If readers need signpost, flag **Plotwright** or **Art/Audio** with hook—don't over-explain via codex.
- **Respect lanes:**
  - Canon/backstory → Lore Weaver
  - Terminology/voice → Style Lead
  - Performance → Player-Narrator
  - Structure → Plotwright
- **Accessibility always:** Meaningful headings, descriptive links ("See Salvage Permits" not "see here"), simple sentences.
- **Anchor hygiene:** Stable kebab-case slugs; notify Binder if renaming.

